==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nunchion
<hw>Nun"chion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>nonechenche</ets>, for <ets>noneschenche</ets>, prop., a noon
drink; <ets>none</ets> noon + <ets>schenchen</ets>, <ets>schenken</ets>,
<ets>skinken</ets>, to pour, AS. <ets>scencan</ets>. See <er>Noon</er>,
and <er>Skink</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <def>A portion of food taken
at or after noon, usually between full meals; a luncheon.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>noonshun</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Hudibras.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nunciate</ent>⟦br⟧
